column5: The son insisted I take one day of the long weekend for myself and do some serious fishing. Off to Orillia at 6 in the morning towing his 12' tinny and makeshift trailer. Despite a slow morning, the afternoon bite was hot. A lot of quality 10-12" fish, and a 14" to boot.   Caught more than enough for 2 hours late night cleaning.
Nice clean looking perch, good eats!!
Nice haul.  Did they have white grub?
Nice !!!! What time is perch dinner at ?? Lol ...cheers !!!!

~~~Hey sorry I missed brekie, I'll try and make it next time. Strange though I followed your directions and ended up in Little Britian. Any way great post, I'll be out Sat. out of Pephpherlaw, off the river mouth
